result.name: Mayfair Gardens

reviews.text: The estate was far away from the MTR station, situated in the hillside.  Transportation was acceptable.  Some restaurants and shops were available to serve the residents and school nearby.  The outlook of the buildings was smart after renovation.  However, the condition of the toilets in the shopping arcade remained extremely bad.
Very good to live. Love to live in Mayfair garden. Good view.

Many restaurants at podium floor. Korea, Thailand, Japan, Western Fine dinning, Rice noodle, Fairwood, Taiwan, 港式茶餐廳, Pizza shop.
IVE and THEi College nearby has ~1km round trip, hill view,  running path for public.
A small private housing estate with a lot of small restaurants. There are Fairwood, 7-eleven, 759...
Small shopping center but good enough to buy daily necessities here
